[
    {
        "text": "On a microscopic level,",
        "start": 1.0,
        "duration": 1.58
    },
    {
        "text": "the Earth’s spin rate",
        "start": 2.58,
        "duration": 1.0
    },
    {
        "text": "and axis are changing constantly",
        "start": 3.58,
        "duration": 2.26
    },
    {
        "text": "The drift of continents,",
        "start": 5.84,
        "duration": 1.3
    },
    {
        "text": "changes in ocean currents,",
        "start": 7.14,
        "duration": 1.48
    },
    {
        "text": "and the rebounding of the crust",
        "start": 8.62,
        "duration": 1.46
    },
    {
        "text": "since the retreat of ice-age glaciers,",
        "start": 10.08,
        "duration": 2.16
    },
    {
        "text": "all shift mass around and",
        "start": 12.24,
        "duration": 1.6
    },
    {
        "text": "alter Earth’s spin rate and axis.",
        "start": 13.84,
        "duration": 2.5
    },
    {
        "text": "Even hurricanes and earthquakes",
        "start": 16.34,
        "duration": 1.68
    },
    {
        "text": "can give the Earth a tiny nudge",
        "start": 18.02,
        "duration": 1.52
    },
    {
        "text": "this way or that.",
        "start": 19.54,
        "duration": 1.72
    },
    {
        "text": "We need this exact information to launch rockets",
        "start": 21.26,
        "duration": 3.12
    },
    {
        "text": "Without these corrections",
        "start": 24.38,
        "duration": 1.06
    },
    {
        "text": "GPS satellites would drift into irrelevance",
        "start": 25.44,
        "duration": 2.2
    },
    {
        "text": "within weeks",
        "start": 27.64,
        "duration": 1.56
    },
    {
        "text": "Right now we rely on",
        "start": 29.2,
        "duration": 1.3
    },
    {
        "text": "“Very Long Baseline Interferometry”",
        "start": 30.5,
        "duration": 2.76
    },
    {
        "text": "to track Earth’s rotation and spin axis",
        "start": 33.26,
        "duration": 3.64
    },
    {
        "text": "But the system requires dozens of observatories",
        "start": 36.9,
        "duration": 2.22
    },
    {
        "text": "to give up valuable astronomy time.",
        "start": 39.12,
        "duration": 2.2
    },
    {
        "text": "And computing the results can sometimes take days.",
        "start": 41.32,
        "duration": 3.56
    },
    {
        "text": "By contrast,",
        "start": 44.88,
        "duration": 1.16
    },
    {
        "text": "the ROMY ring laser promises to make fast",
        "start": 46.04,
        "duration": 2.62
    },
    {
        "text": "and potentially continuous measurements.",
        "start": 48.66,
        "duration": 3.4
    },
    {
        "text": "This is ROMY",
        "start": 52.06,
        "duration": 0.76
    },
    {
        "text": "being built over the course of 6 months",
        "start": 52.82,
        "duration": 2.9
    },
    {
        "text": "At the end it’s buried underground",
        "start": 55.72,
        "duration": 1.48
    },
    {
        "text": "with only a few access points sticking up.",
        "start": 57.2,
        "duration": 3.0
    },
    {
        "text": "Last month, it turned on all four of its",
        "start": 60.2,
        "duration": 2.0
    },
    {
        "text": "triangular laser rings for the first time.",
        "start": 62.2,
        "duration": 3.12
    },
    {
        "text": "ROMY, like other ring lasers,",
        "start": 65.32,
        "duration": 1.76
    },
    {
        "text": "relies on the Sagnac effect,",
        "start": 67.08,
        "duration": 2.0
    },
    {
        "text": "in which two beams travel in",
        "start": 69.08,
        "duration": 1.34
    },
    {
        "text": "opposite directions around the same path",
        "start": 70.42,
        "duration": 2.94
    },
    {
        "text": "Because the Earth is rotating",
        "start": 73.36,
        "duration": 1.3
    },
    {
        "text": "in the direction of one of the lasers,",
        "start": 74.66,
        "duration": 1.78
    },
    {
        "text": "it incurs an extra path length",
        "start": 76.44,
        "duration": 1.92
    },
    {
        "text": "that the laser accommodates",
        "start": 78.36,
        "duration": 1.32
    },
    {
        "text": "by stretching\nits wavelengths",
        "start": 79.68,
        "duration": 1.6
    },
    {
        "text": "and lowering its frequency.",
        "start": 81.28,
        "duration": 2.18
    },
    {
        "text": "The frequency of the counter-rotating laser rises",
        "start": 83.46,
        "duration": 3.7
    },
    {
        "text": "When interfered,",
        "start": 87.16,
        "duration": 0.94
    },
    {
        "text": "the slightly clashing lasers",
        "start": 88.1,
        "duration": 1.46
    },
    {
        "text": "frequencies create beats --",
        "start": 89.56,
        "duration": 2.08
    },
    {
        "text": "the same pulsing beats that piano tuners",
        "start": 91.64,
        "duration": 1.92
    },
    {
        "text": "try to eliminate",
        "start": 93.56,
        "duration": 1.18
    },
    {
        "text": "as they strike a note and a tuning fork",
        "start": 94.74,
        "duration": 1.82
    },
    {
        "text": "at the same time.",
        "start": 96.56,
        "duration": 1.8
    },
    {
        "text": "The beat frequency is a direct measure",
        "start": 98.36,
        "duration": 2.0
    },
    {
        "text": "of the rotation that causes it.",
        "start": 100.36,
        "duration": 2.5
    },
    {
        "text": "With its 12 meter arms,",
        "start": 102.86,
        "duration": 1.4
    },
    {
        "text": "ROMY is more sensitive than smaller ring lasers.",
        "start": 104.26,
        "duration": 3.14
    },
    {
        "text": "And instead of one square ring,",
        "start": 107.42,
        "duration": 1.96
    },
    {
        "text": "it has four triangular ones.",
        "start": 109.38,
        "duration": 2.78
    },
    {
        "text": "Three are required to pin down",
        "start": 112.16,
        "duration": 1.3
    },
    {
        "text": "rotations in any direction,",
        "start": 113.46,
        "duration": 1.66
    },
    {
        "text": "while the fourth adds redundancy.",
        "start": 115.12,
        "duration": 2.6
    },
    {
        "text": "Being so new, however,",
        "start": 117.72,
        "duration": 1.2
    },
    {
        "text": "ROMY is plagued by experimental drift.",
        "start": 118.92,
        "duration": 2.78
    },
    {
        "text": "The machine is settling in soft sediments,",
        "start": 121.7,
        "duration": 2.04
    },
    {
        "text": "and its steel tubes will flex with the temperature",
        "start": 123.74,
        "duration": 2.28
    },
    {
        "text": "swings of day and night.",
        "start": 126.02,
        "duration": 1.8
    },
    {
        "text": "Scientists will try to isolate",
        "start": 127.82,
        "duration": 1.32
    },
    {
        "text": "and eliminate these sources of noise.",
        "start": 129.14,
        "duration": 2.44
    },
    {
        "text": "But there is one type of noise that scientists",
        "start": 131.58,
        "duration": 2.12
    },
    {
        "text": "want ROMY to capture:",
        "start": 133.7,
        "duration": 1.7
    },
    {
        "text": "tilt motions from earthquakes.",
        "start": 135.4,
        "duration": 2.32
    },
    {
        "text": "Traditionally, seismologists",
        "start": 137.72,
        "duration": 1.4
    },
    {
        "text": "could only measure translation,",
        "start": 139.12,
        "duration": 1.74
    },
    {
        "text": "or displacements along any of",
        "start": 140.86,
        "duration": 1.68
    },
    {
        "text": "the three cardinal axes.",
        "start": 142.54,
        "duration": 1.64
    },
    {
        "text": "But earthquakes also contain tilt motions,",
        "start": 144.18,
        "duration": 2.78
    },
    {
        "text": "which rotate the ground without shifting it.",
        "start": 146.96,
        "duration": 2.62
    },
    {
        "text": "Engineers have been designing buildings",
        "start": 149.58,
        "duration": 1.48
    },
    {
        "text": "for only one type of shaking,",
        "start": 151.06,
        "duration": 1.98
    },
    {
        "text": "when really they should be designed",
        "start": 153.04,
        "duration": 1.42
    },
    {
        "text": "for the two different inputs",
        "start": 154.46,
        "duration": 2.04
    },
    {
        "text": "Although ROMY can record these motions",
        "start": 156.5,
        "duration": 1.7
    },
    {
        "text": "from distant earthquakes, it can’t move.",
        "start": 158.2,
        "duration": 2.38
    },
    {
        "text": "That’s why scientists want to build",
        "start": 160.58,
        "duration": 1.7
    },
    {
        "text": "smaller, portable rotation sensors,",
        "start": 162.28,
        "duration": 2.44
    },
    {
        "text": "based on fiber optics,",
        "start": 164.72,
        "duration": 1.26
    },
    {
        "text": "that could be sent out to measure tilt motions",
        "start": 165.98,
        "duration": 2.22
    },
    {
        "text": "around the world.",
        "start": 168.2,
        "duration": 1.4
    }
]